#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn24.7"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn24.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 24 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 24 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Sotāpattivagga "
msgstr "1. Stream-Entry "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn24.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Hetusutta "
msgstr "7. Cause "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.210, sc1
msgctxt "sn24.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:1.2"
msgid "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise: "

msgctxt "sn24.7:1.3"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya. "
msgstr "‘There is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "sn24.7:1.4"
msgid "Ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti. "
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or reason. "

msgctxt "sn24.7:1.5"
msgid "Natthi hetu, natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā. "
msgstr "There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "sn24.7:1.6"
msgid "Ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhanti. "
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified without cause or reason. "

msgctxt "sn24.7:1.7"
msgid "Natthi balaṃ natthi vīriyaṃ natthi purisathāmo natthi purisaparakkamo. "
msgstr "There is no power, no energy, no manly strength or vigor. "

msgctxt "sn24.7:1.8"
msgid "Sabbe sattā sabbe pāṇā sabbe bhūtā sabbe jīvā avasā abalā avīriyā niyatisaṅgatibhāvapariṇatā chasvevābhijātīsu sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’”ti? "
msgstr "All sentient beings, all living creatures, all beings, all souls lack control, power, and energy. Molded by destiny, circumstance, and nature, they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:1.9"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn24.7:2.1"
msgid "“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.2"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo … pe … "
msgstr "‘There is no cause or condition … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.3"
msgid "sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti. "
msgstr "they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’ "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.4"
msgid "Vedanāya sati … pe … "
msgstr "When feeling … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.5"
msgid "saññāya sati … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.6"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.7"
msgid "viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.8"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo … pe … "
msgstr "‘There is no cause or condition … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:2.9"
msgid "sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’ti. "
msgstr "they experience pleasure and pain in the six classes of rebirth.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.4"
msgid "vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.5"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.6"
msgid "sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.7"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.8"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.9"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.10"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.11"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.12"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.13"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.14"
msgid "‘natthi hetu, natthi paccayo … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.15"
msgid "sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’”ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.16"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.17"
msgid "“Yampidaṃ diṭṭhaṃ sutaṃ mutaṃ viññātaṃ pattaṃ pariyesitaṃ anuvicaritaṃ manasā tampi niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“That which is seen, heard, thought, known, sought, and explored by the mind: is that permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.18"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.19"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?” "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.20"
msgid "‘natthi hetu natthi paccayo … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn24.7:3.21"
msgid "sukhadukkhaṃ paṭisaṃvedentī’”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.7:3.22"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.211, sc4
msgctxt "sn24.7:4.1"
msgid "“Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa imesu ca ṭhānesu kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti, dukkhepissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāyapissa kaṅkhā pahīnā hoti—"
msgstr "“When a noble disciple has given up doubt in these six cases, and has given up doubt in suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the practice that leads to its cessation, "

msgctxt "sn24.7:4.2"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti. "
msgstr "they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn24.7:4.3"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

